com.proximyst.sewer.loadable

Class Loadable<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.proximyst.sewer.loadable.Loadable<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type to be loaded.

    public class Loadable<T>
extends Object
    A type loaded lazily using a SewerSystem as a pipeline.

    This runs everything as async and lazy by default. To run this on the application's "main thread", it must somehow accept tasks through an Executor.

      • builder

        public static <Input,Output> @NonNull Loadable.Builder<Loadable<Input>,Output> builder(@NonNull SewerSystem<Input,Output> system,
                                                                                       Loadable<Input> input)
        Create a new builder.
        Type Parameters:
        Input - The input to accept to load the value. This is not set to null and is therefore not recommended to be a large value one wants garbage collected.
        Output - The type of the Loadable.
        Parameters:
        system - The SewerSystem pipeline to use for loading the value.
        input - The Input value for loading the value in the form of another Loadable. The value must therefore be loaded through that before it can be loaded with this. If the other Loadable is not already loaded, this will wait for it to load.
        Returns:
        A new Loadable.Builder to create a new Loadable.

      • getOrLoadResult

        public CompletableFuture<PipeResult<T>> getOrLoadResult()
        Gets the internal state or loads it if non-existent before returning its value in the form of a CompletableFuture.

        If this has no loaded value, it will initiate one and fill a CompletableFuture with it. If it is already loaded, an existing, cached CompletableFuture will be returned instead.

        Returns:
        A future with the PipeResult of the loading process.
        See Also:
        isLoaded(), getOrLoad()

      • getOrLoad

        public CompletableFuture<Optional<T>> getOrLoad()
        Gets the internal state or loads it if non-existent before returning its value in the form of a CompletableFuture.

        If this has no loaded value, it will initiate one and fill a CompletableFuture with it. If it is already loaded, an existing, cached CompletableFuture will be returned instead.

        If the loading process threw an Exception, the future will be completed with it. Any CompletableFuture.join() will therefore also throw this Exception. Any null values will be thrown out, and if it has been filtered out, Optional.empty() is returned.

        Returns:
        A future with the returned value of the loading process.
        See Also:
        isLoaded(), getOrLoadResult()
